In the case as below:
a = data + data;
b = a + data;
c = b +data;
res = c +data;
data_cache = cache_read(data); ---- reader list(a, b, c, res)

It need to replace dataflow for all ops when the tensor data_cache is created. The original dataflow replacement algorithm for the case is shown as below:

1) Create the vmap<tensor, tensor> [(data, data_cache)], then replace "data" with "data_cache" for all op in readers, and the vmap will be [(data, data_cache), (a, a1), (b, b1), (c, c1), (res, res1)]
2) Come into the function ReplaceDataFlow, for data, data_cache, a, there is no change.  But in b's turn, it need to replace b's input a to a1, and create b2 to replace b1, the vmap will be [(data, data_cache), (a, a1), (b, b1), (b1, b2), (c, c1), (res, res1)]. In c's turn, it should be use b2 to replace its input b, but it can only get b1 by the key b in vmap. So after b's turn, the expected vmap should be [(data, data_cache), (a, a1), (b, b2), (c, c1), (res, res1)], and so on.

I maintained a reverse vmap to record (b1, b), then update vmap (b, b1) to (b, b2).
